# Notification Bell — Badge + Dropdown

## Overview

Both `voucher.html` and `purchase_request.html` have a red bell badge in the top nav (desktop and mobile) that shows the count of items requiring the current user's action. Clicking the bell opens a dropdown panel listing each pending item by number; clicking a row opens the detail directly.

## HTML Structure

Inserted in `#nav-user-section` (desktop) and in the mobile nav right-side flex div.

```html
<div id="notif-bell-wrapper" onclick="toggleNotifDropdown() /* or _toggleNotifDropdown() */" style="position:relative;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;cursor:pointer;padding:4px;">
    <i class="fas fa-bell" style="font-size:18px;color:#6e6e73;"></i>
    <span id="notif-badge" style="display:none;position:absolute;top:-6px;right:-7px;...">0</span>
    <div id="notif-dropdown" style="display:none;position:absolute;top:calc(100% + 10px);right:0;width:280px;...">
        <div>Việc cần làm của tôi</div>
        <div id="notif-dropdown-body" style="max-height:320px;overflow-y:auto;"></div>
    </div>
</div>
<!-- Mobile: separate <span id="notif-badge-mobile"> in mobile nav -->
```

## JavaScript Functions

### `voucher.html`

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `_pendingVoucherItems(vouchers)` | Filters `allLoadedVouchers` to those needing the current user's action |
| `countMyPendingVoucherActions(vouchers)` | Returns `.length` of above |
| `updateNotifBadge(count, items)` | Updates both badges + rebuilds `#notif-dropdown-body` |
| `toggleNotifDropdown()` | Toggles `#notif-dropdown` display |

Called at end of `updateVoucherStats(vouchers)`.

### `purchase_request.html`

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `_pendingPRItems(list)` | Filters `_allPRs` to those needing the current user's action |
| `_countPendingPRActions(list)` | Returns `.length` of above |
| `_updateNotifBadge(count, items)` | Updates both badges + rebuilds `#notif-dropdown-body` |
| `_toggleNotifDropdown()` | Toggles `#notif-dropdown` display |

Called at end of `_updatePRStats(list)`.

Both pages also attach a `document.addEventListener('click', ...)` that closes the dropdown when clicking outside `#notif-bell-wrapper`.

## What Counts as "My Pending Action"

### Vouchers
Role is determined by `getCallerRole()` (reads `tlc_current_user` from localStorage):
- `accountant` → vouchers with `progressNum === 0`
- `legalRep` → vouchers with `progressNum === 1`
- `treasurer` → vouchers with `progressNum === 2`
- `admin` → vouchers at `progressNum === 0` that are not rejected
- `submitter` → not counted (they see their own flow in the list itself)

### PRs
Mirrors the exact gate logic in `renderPRDrawer`:
- `parallel` stage: email matches `budgetApproverEmail` and `budgetStatus !== 'Approved'`
- `parallel` stage: email matches `supplierApproverEmail` and `supplierStatus !== 'Approved'`
- `contract` stage: email matches `contractApproverEmail`
- `purchasing` stage: email matches `purchasingApproverEmail`
- Any stage: `status === 'trả lại bổ sung'` and `requestorEmail === myEmail` (submitter needs to resubmit)

## Dropdown Row Behavior

- **Vouchers:** shows voucher number (blue) + type + company; click calls `openVoucherDetail(voucherNumber)`
- **PRs:** shows PR number (blue) + company; "Trả lại" amber tag for returned PRs; click calls `openPRDrawer(prNo)`
- Capped at 15 rows; shows "+N phiếu khác" if more
- Empty state: "Không có việc cần làm"

## CSS Classes

- `voucher.html`: `.notif-item` — hover highlight, border-bottom separator
- `purchase_request.html`: `.pr-notif-item` — same pattern

## Badge IDs

| ID | Location |
|---|---|
| `notif-badge` | Desktop nav (both pages) |
| `notif-badge-mobile` | Mobile nav (both pages) |
| `notif-dropdown` | Dropdown panel wrapper |
| `notif-dropdown-body` | Scrollable content area inside panel |
| `notif-bell-wrapper` | Clickable bell container (click-outside detection anchor) |

## Rules

- **Do not** add a separate backend call for the count — it is always derived from already-loaded data (`allLoadedVouchers` / `_allPRs`).
- **Do not** change the count logic independently of `renderPRDrawer` gate checks — they must stay in sync.
- If a new approval stage is added to either flow, update both `_pendingVoucherItems` / `_pendingPRItems` AND `renderPRDrawer` / the voucher approval logic together.
